from dbd david davidian subject account of anti-armenian human right violation in azerbaijan account of anti-armenian human right violation in azerbaijan prelude to current event in nagorno-karabakh on the way the driver say in fact there be any armenian leave burn them all beat them all and stab them deposition of vanya bagratovich bazian born foreman baku spetsmontazh administration resident at building apartment block sumgait azerbaijan during the first day of the event the and the of february i wa away on a busines trip on the i have get my crew do the paper work and leave for the zhdanov district that in azerbaijan near the nagorno karabagh region after the rumor start to the effect that in karabagh specifically in stepanakert an uprise have take place they say uprise in azerbaijani but i do think it wa really an uprise just a demonstration after that the unrest start several armenian live in the zhdanov district be injure how be they injure they be beat even woman it wa say that they be at the demonstration but they live here and go from here to karabagh to demonstrate after that i felt uneasy there be some conversation about armenian among the local population the armenian have do thi the armenian have do that right there at the site i wa attack a couple of time by kid well true the guy from my crew would let them come at me with cable and knife after that i felt really bad i do know where to go i up and call home and my child tell me there unrest everywhere be careful well i have a project go on i tell the second secretary of the district party committee what have be go on and say i want to take my crew off the site they would allow it they say nothing go to happen to you we entrust the matter to the polouse we warn everyone in the district nothing will happen to you well in fact they do especially detail u a policeman to look after me he know all the local person and would protect me if something happen thi man do leave me alone for five minute he wa at work the whole time and afterward he spend the night with u too i sense some disquiet and call home my wife also tell me the situation be very tense be careful we finish the job at the site and i leave for sumgait first thing on the morning of the when we leave the guy warn me they tell me that i should tell anyone on the way that i wa an armenian i take someone else busines travel document in the name of zardali and hide my own i hide it and my passport in my sock we set out for baku my guy be on the bu they sit behind and i sit up front in baku they have come to me and say that they have to collect all of my travel document just in case a it turn out they know what wa happen in sumgait i arrive at the bu station and there they tell me that the city of sumgait be close there be no way to get there that the city be close off and the bus be run bus normally leave baku for sumgait almost every two minute and suddenly no bus well we try to get there vium private driver one man an azerbaijani say let go find some other way to get there they find a light transport vehicle and arrange for the driver to take u to sumgait he take u there but the other have say i would go if you give me a thousand ruble why because they burn the city and kill the armenian there be an armenian leave well i get hold of myself so i could still stand up so we square it away the fmy of u get in the car and we set off for sumgait on the way the driver say in fact there be any armenian leave burn them all beat them all and stab them well i wa silent the whole way mile i wa silent the driver ask me how old be you old man he want to know if i be that quiet not say anything maybe it mean i an armenian how old be you he ask me i say i i too but i call you man i say it depend on god each person life in thi world be different i look much older than my year that why he call me old man well after that he wa silent too we approach the city i look and see tank all around and a cordon before we get to the kavkaz store the driver start to wave hi hand well he wa wave hi hand we all start wave my hand i sit there with them i start wave my hand too i realize that thi wa a sign that mean there be no armenian with u i look at the city there be a crowd of person walk down the middle of the street you know and there no traffic well probably i wa scar they stop my car person be stand on the sidewalk they have armature shaft and stone and they stop u along the way the driver tell u how they know who an armenian and who not the armenian usually for example i an armenian but i speak their language very well well armenian usually pronounce the azerus word for nut or little nut a pundukh but fundukh be actually correct the pronunciation be different anyone who say pundukh even if they not armenian they immediately take out and start to slash another one say there wa a car there with five person inside it he say they start hit the side of it with an axe and light it on fire and they do let the person out he say they would let them get out of the car i only saw the car but the driver say that he saw everything well he often drife from baku to sumgait and back when they stop u we all get out of the car i look and there a short guy hi eye be gleam he ha an armature shaft in one hand and a stone in the other and ask the guy what nationality they be one by one we azerbaijani they tell him armenian here he do come up to me when we be pull my thing out and say maybe you an armenian old man but in azerbaijani i say you should be ashamed of yourself and he leave turned and leave that wa all that happen what wa i to do i have to the city wa on fire but i have to steal my child out of my own home they stop u at the entrance to mir street that where the kavkaz store and three large build be that the begin of down-town i saw that burn automobile there completely burn only metal remain i could figure out if it wa a zhiguli or a zaporozhet later i wa tell it wa a zhiguli and the person in there be completely incinerate nothing remain of them not even any trace that driver have tell me about it and i saw the car myself the car wa there the skeleton a metallic carcas about to yard from the kavkaz store i see a military transport an armor personnel carrier the hatch be close and person be throw armature shaft and piece of iron at it the crowd be and i hear shoot not automatic fire it true but pistol shoot several shoot there be azerbaijani crowd around that personnel carrier someone in the crowd wa shoot apparently they either want to kill the soldier or get a machine gun or something at that point there wa only one armor personnel carrier and all the tank be outside the city cordoning off sumgait i walk on i see two azerbaijani go home from the plant i can tell by their gait that they not bandit they just person walk home i join them so in case something happen in case someone come up to u and ask question either of u would be in a position to answer you see but i avoid the large group because i a local and might be quickly recognize i try to keep at a distance and walk where there be fewer person well so i walk into microdistrict which be acros from my block i ca get into my block but i walk where there be fewer person so a to get around well there i see a tall guy and to person be walk behind him and he shout into a megaphone comrade the armenian azerbaijani war ha begin the polouse have megaphone like that so they talk and walk around the second microdistrict i see that they come my way and turn off behind a build i notice that they walk around the outside build and inside the microdistrict there be about or person stand on every corner and at the middle of the build and at the edge what they be do i ca say because i could get up close to them i wa afraid but the most important thing wa to get away from there to get home and at least find out if my child be alive or not april yerevan reference the sumgait tragedy pogrom against armenian in soviet azerbaijan volume i eyewitnes account edit by samuel shahmuradian forward by yelena bonner publish by aristide d caratza ny page david davidian dbd how do we explain turkish troop on center for regional study the armenian border when we ca box even explain cambridge ma turkish mp march 